    <tabSettings>
        <tab>standard-Lead</tab>
        <visibility>Visible</visibility>
    </tabSettings>
    <tabSettings>
        <tab>standard-Quote</tab>
        <visibility>Visible</visibility>
    </tabSettings>
    <tabSettings>
        <tab>standard-Campaign</tab>
        <visibility>Visible</visibility>
    </tabSettings>

    <!--
    TESTING CHECKLIST:
    □ 1. Create test sales user
    □ 2. Assign this permission set
    □ 3. Test lead creation and conversion
    □ 4. Test opportunity creation and editing
    □ 5. Test account and contact management
    □ 6. Test quote creation
    □ 7. Test task/event logging
    □ 8. Test report access
    □ 9. Test mobile access (if applicable)
    □ 10. Test forecast access (if using forecasts)
    □ 11. Verify territory access (if using territories)
    □ 12. Test CPQ functionality (if using Salesforce CPQ)

    TERRITORY MANAGEMENT:
    If using Enterprise Territory Management:
    - Set ViewAllRecords=true on Account/Opportunity for territory-wide visibility
    - Or configure territory-based sharing rules
    - Consider creating separate permission sets per territory

    FORECASTING:
    If using Collaborative Forecasts:
    - Enable ViewAllForecasts for managers
    - Enable EditMyForecasts for forecast submission
    - Configure forecast categories

    SALESFORCE CPQ:
    If using Salesforce CPQ (formerly SteelBrick):
    - Add SBQQ objects (SBQQ__Quote__c, SBQQ__QuoteLine__c)
    - Grant appropriate CPQ permissions
    - Configure price book access

    BEST PRACTICES:
    - Combine with role hierarchy for team visibility
    - Use sharing rules for cross-team collaboration
    - Configure opportunity teams for deal collaboration
    - Set up account teams for strategic accounts
    - Enable activity tracking for pipeline management

    MAINTENANCE:
    - Review quarterly for new sales processes
    - Audit field permissions for custom fields
    - Update as sales cloud features evolve
    - Track permission set usage and effectiveness
    -->
</PermissionSet>
